      • cloneViaReserialise

        public Record cloneViaReserialise()
        Clone the current record, via a call to serialize it, and another to create a new record from the bytes. May only be used for classes which don't have internal counts / ids in them. For those which do, a full model-aware cloning is needed, which allocates new ids / counts as needed.(${t_0a60f78e6ffb46b49ba32063f0a8b78f})
        Returns:
        the cloned current record(${t_7c08e3e513da4e11b1ca6b4c95ab46e7})
